Developing a full WhatsApp clone in React Native would be quite extensive, but I can provide you with a simple example that demonstrates some key features like sending and receiving messages. Here's a basic code snippet to get you started:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { View, TextInput, FlatList, StyleSheet, TouchableOpacity, Text } from 'react-native';

const ChatScreen = () => {
  const [messages, setMessages] = useState([]);
  const [inputText, setInputText] = useState('');

  const handleSend = () => {
    if (inputText.trim() !== '') {
      setMessages(prevMessages => [...prevMessages, inputText]);
      setInputText('');
    }
  };

  const renderMessage = ({ item }) => (
    <View style={styles.messageContainer}>
      <Text style={styles.messageText}>{item}</Text>
    </View>
  );

  return (
    <View style={styles.container}>
      <FlatList
        data={messages}
        renderItem={renderMessage}
        keyExtractor={(item, index) => index.toString()}
        contentContainerStyle={styles.messagesContainer}
        inverted
      />
      <View style={styles.inputContainer}>
        <TextInput
          style={styles.textInput}
          value={inputText}
          onChangeText={setInputText}
          placeholder="Type a message..."
        />
        <TouchableOpacity style={styles.sendButton} onPress={handleSend}>
          <Text style={styles.sendButtonText}>Send</Text>
        </TouchableOpacity>
      </View>
    </View>
  );
};

const styles = StyleSheet.create({
  container: {
    flex: 1,
    justifyContent: 'center',
  },
  messagesContainer: {
    padding: 10,
    flexGrow: 1,
  },
  messageContainer: {
    backgroundColor: '#e5e5e5',
    borderRadius: 10,
    paddingHorizontal: 15,
    paddingVertical: 10,
    marginBottom: 10,
  },
  messageText: {
    fontSize: 16,
    color: '#333',
  },
  inputContainer: {
    flexDirection: 'row',
    alignItems: 'center',
    borderTopWidth: 1,
    borderTopColor: '#ccc',
    padding: 10,
  },
  textInput: {
    flex: 1,
    borderRadius: 10,
    backgroundColor: '#f0f0f0',
    paddingHorizontal: 10,
    paddingVertical: 7,
    marginRight: 10,
  },
  sendButton: {
    backgroundColor: '#007BFF',
    borderRadius: 10,
    paddingVertical: 7,
    paddingHorizontal: 10,
  },
  sendButtonText: {
    color: '#fff',
    fontSize: 16,
    fontWeight: 'bold',
  },
});

export default ChatScreen;
```

This code sets up a chat screen where users can send and receive messages. It uses state to store the input text and the messages. Messages are rendered using `FlatList` and new messages can be sent by typing in the input box and pressing the send button.

Please note that this is a simplified example and there are many other features and functionalities that a full-fledged WhatsApp clone would require.
